# Expense Tracker

## Project Description

This project is a Full Stack Expense Tracker built using the MERN stack. It allows users to create, view, update, and delete expenses, track spending by category, visualize spending patterns through charts, and filter expenses using category and date ranges. The application provides a dashboard-style interface for managing personal expenses efficiently.

---

## Live Demo Links

Frontend: https://your-frontend-url.vercel.app

Backend: https://your-backend-url.onrender.com

---

## Tech Stack

### Frontend

* React.js
* Vite
* Axios
* Tailwind CSS
* Recharts

### Backend

* Node.js
* Express.js
* MongoDB
* Mongoose

### Why These Technologies

* React provides a component-based UI architecture.
* Express simplifies API development.
* MongoDB offers flexible document storage.
* Axios handles API communication.
* Tailwind CSS enables rapid UI development.
* Recharts provides easy-to-use chart components.

---

## Features

* Add Expenses
* Edit Expenses
* Delete Expenses
* View Expense History
* Category-Based Filtering
* Date Range Filtering
* Expense Summary Dashboard
* Spending Visualization with Pie Chart
* Currency Formatting
* Form Validation

---

## How to Run Locally

### Clone Repository

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd mini-expense-tracker
```

### Backend Setup

```bash
cd backend
npm install
```

Create a `.env` file:

```env
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
```

Start backend:

```bash
npm start
```

### Frontend Setup

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Frontend runs on:

```text
http://localhost:5173
```

Backend runs on:

```text
http://localhost:5000
```

---

## API Documentation

### Get All Expenses

```http
GET /api/expenses
```

Response:

```json
{
  "expenses": []
}
```

---

### Create Expense

```http
POST /api/expenses
```

Request:

```json
{
  "amount": 500,
  "category": "Food",
  "date": "2026-06-02",
  "note": "Lunch"
}
```

---

### Update Expense

```http
PUT /api/expenses/:id
```

Request:

```json
{
  "amount": 1000,
  "category": "Bills",
  "date": "2026-06-02",
  "note": "Electricity Bill"
}
```

---

### Delete Expense

```http
DELETE /api/expenses/:id
```

---

### Expense Summary

```http
GET /api/expenses/summary
```

Response:

```json
{
  "totalSpent": 2469,
  "highestExpense": {},
  "categoryTotals": {}
}
```

